KEd The Kudzu Editor for OS/2
    by Kudzu Software

KEd is a shareware character mode text editor for OS/2 2.x and 3.x, designed 
for speed and ease of use. It is a full 32-bit application, and features 
support for HPFS filenames, keystroke macros, up to 96 open files, 
huge (32MB) file sizes, extensive support of cut and paste blocks of lines
or columns, and shelling to a command processor prompt. 
User configurable settings can be saved to an INI file, and there is 
extensive on-line hypertext help for ease of use.  

On-Line versions are fully functional!
Registered users worldwide, shipping since August 1993.
Shareware registration $20. 
